00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:58.980
So where should you start
with the design process?

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:02.795
A clue can actually come here
from motivational psychology,

00:08:02.795 --> 00:08:05.440
of all things.

00:08:05.440 --> 00:08:07.850
Some of you might be familiar
with Maslow's

00:08:07.850 --> 00:08:09.590
Hierarchy of Needs.

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:13.450
Basically postulates that all
human behavior is geared

00:08:13.450 --> 00:08:17.900
towards sort of fulfilling basic
needs first before you

00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:22.710
progress to the higher levels,
the higher needs.

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:27.630
So for example, before I take
care of the safety of my

00:08:27.630 --> 00:08:31.450
employment, I probably want to
breathe, eat, and sleep.

00:08:31.450 --> 00:08:35.039
So these so the more
basic needs here.

00:08:35.039 --> 00:08:37.669
So you might ask now,
what does that have

00:08:37.669 --> 00:08:38.980
to do with app design?

00:08:38.980 --> 00:08:39.929
And that's a good question.

00:08:39.929 --> 00:08:42.970
But it is the principle
of how you should

00:08:42.970 --> 00:08:45.280
approach app design.

00:08:45.280 --> 00:08:47.830
App designers really should
address their apps' design

00:08:47.830 --> 00:08:52.745
needs by progressing through a
similar Hierarchy of Needs.

00:08:52.745 --> 00:08:56.120
The contents here, of course,
are a little bit different.

00:08:56.120 --> 00:08:58.890
So you should address the
design foundations first

00:08:58.890 --> 00:09:03.040
before striving to address
higher level needs.

00:09:03.040 --> 00:09:07.770
In this pyramid, if you just
cover the first three levels

00:09:07.770 --> 00:09:11.150
of the pyramid, you already have
a really competitive app

00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:15.380
that measures up against
the competition well.

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:19.720
And it will be also an app that
is sort of a good citizen

00:09:19.720 --> 00:09:23.960
on the Android platform in that
it sort of follows the

00:09:23.960 --> 00:09:28.100
rules and regulations
of the UI.

00:09:28.100 --> 00:09:30.890
The Android Design Guide, which
you hear about more in a

00:09:30.890 --> 00:09:34.010
second, sort of gets you
to that third level.

00:09:34.010 --> 00:09:38.080
It mainly deals with the second
and the third tier of

00:09:38.080 --> 00:09:41.530
this pyramid.

00:09:41.530 --> 00:09:47.240
So as a takeaway, make sure
that you cover your bases.

00:09:47.240 --> 00:09:48.970
So before you do this--

00:09:48.970 --> 00:09:50.510
and that might an instinct.

00:09:50.510 --> 00:09:54.150
Everybody wants the pretty app
that does exciting things like

00:09:54.150 --> 00:09:55.600
nice transitions
and everything.

00:09:55.600 --> 00:10:01.450
But before you do this, really
make sure that you do that.

00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:04.340
The base of the pyramid.

00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:06.930
Because if you don't do that,
that often equals the

